---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 36
By: Râmânanda Ray
Tags:
  - Creation=Creation as Play or Sport
---
I am a dancer and you are the manager of the theatre; I dance as you make me.
My tongue is merely a harp, and you (Krishna) are the musician who plays on it.
I utter whatever you think in your mind.
